The paper proposes a method for distilling ensembles of models into a single compact model, which is a common problem in machine learning and falls under the category of model compression. The proposed method is based on a multi-headed neural network, which is a popular approach in deep learning and falls under the category of neural networks. The paper also evaluates the proposed method on classification and regression tasks, which are common problems in machine learning and fall under the categories of supervised learning and predictive modeling. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.CL (Computation and Language).
